1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
What happens to your body at high altitudes?

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:05,200
It’s not what you think.

3
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:10,400
Acclimatization altitude is where your body struggles to adapt to lower oxygen levels.

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:13,600
At 8,000 feet, many feel dizzy and fatigued.

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:14,400
But why?

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,000
Let’s break it down.

7
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Your body increases red blood cells, but this takes time.

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,600
Some adapt, some don’t.

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,200
Inconsistent outcomes create uncertainty.

10
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,800
It’s a complex process influenced by genetics and duration.

11
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,400
Curious about your limits?

12
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:31,200
Like and follow for more science insights!
